    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="824"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d824">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1703a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed that in cases of seizure since blockade order in council,
                    prize court proceedings are based both on violation of blockade and on suspected
                    contraband character of goods. Investigate and report any cases in which both
                    grounds of seizure are stated in same writ.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
